@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place "GridBlock" where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

                             How to play?

  Playing the game is pretty simple: click on the bar you want to
move, if it is located next to the empty space, the bar will move
towards that position. If a bar is at the edge of the game board
and the empty space is at the opposite edge on the same row or
column, with the bar, the bar will 'wrap around' the edge towards
the other edge. The same thing happens if the bar is 'halfway
across' at the edges, and the empty space is next to it. Note that
you can also use the cursor keys to move the bars in the game...

  When the empty space is located at a corner space of the game
board, the border of that corner will 'blow-up' and the corner
will be unlocked.

  You can restart a puzzle any time by clicking on the 'New Game'
button (or with the right-Amiga and "N" keys), this will redisplay
a puzzle as it was at the start.

  Try to complete each of the puzzles in the least amount of moves
possible.

  Have fun!

@endnode

